        <name>7.3.4.3 Exercise 3</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Find the cofactors of \(x,y,z\) in the following determinant:&lt;/p&gt;
\[\begin{vmatrix} {@AA[1,1]@} &amp;amp; {@AA[1,2]@} &amp;amp; {@AA[1,3]@} \\ {@AA[2,1]@} &amp;amp; {@AA[2,2]@} &amp;amp; {@AA[2,3]@} \\ x &amp;amp; y &amp;amp; z \end{vmatrix}\]

&lt;p&gt;Cofactor of \(x\): [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cofactor of \(y\): [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cofactor of \(z\): [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]&lt;/p&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>To obtain the cofactor of an element of a \(3 \times 3\) matrix we multiply the minor of that element by the corresponding sign from the \(3 \times 3\) array of signs.&lt;br&gt;We are given the determinant: \(\begin{vmatrix} {@AA[1,1]@} &amp;amp; {@AA[1,2]@} &amp;amp; {@AA[1,3]@} \\ {@AA[2,1]@} &amp;amp; {@AA[2,2]@} &amp;amp; {@AA[2,3]@} \\ x &amp;amp; y &amp;amp; z \end{vmatrix}.\)&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;For \(x\), the sign is \(+\), and the minor is \(\det {@MMx@}\). Hence the cofactor is \({@ta1@}.\)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;For \(y\), the sign is \(-\), and the minor is \(\det {@MMy@}\). Hence the cofactor is \({@ta2@}.\)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;For \(z\), the sign is \(+\) again, and the minor is \(\det {@MMz@}\). Hence the cofactor is \({@ta3@}.\)&lt;/p&gt;</generalfeedback>
